This paper discusses privacy vulnerabilities in encrypted IoT traffic, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also examines network traffic rates of IoT devices, which could be related to information retrieval (cs.IR) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The study of IoT-specific concerns and policy debates around ISP data collection and usage could be categorized under social and information sciences (cs.SI) and cybersecurity (cs.CY).
